						<summary>

						<p>On a stone lying in front of the Āṅjañēya temple near the choultry in the village.</p>						

						<p>This is dated Śaka 1711, Saumya, Jyēshṭha, śu. 15.</p>						

						<p>Records the construction of steps to the Nāgulēru (stream) and installation of Subbarāya at Dāchepalli by Pantulavāru, son of Venkanna Pantulu and grandson of Mṛityunjayadīkshita of Harita<hi rend="italic">gōtra.</hi></p>						

